title: GARAGE SQUAD'S JOE ZOLPER'S DAUNTLESS DAYTONA! STREET OUTLAWS NO PREPS KINGS! RT66 JOLIET!
description: Joe Zolper's '69 Dodge Daytona has made quite the stir on the internet when it was first revealed and garnered plenty of attention at the Street Outlaws No Prep Kings Season 3 event at RT66 Joliet. From it's blown 521ci Hemi to the beautiful destroyer grey paint and iconic black daytona wing it has that gotcha factor not to mention unique! Having only made a couple shakedown passes well before the event and now switching to larger rear slicks and a different suspension setup Joe had no idea what to expect on the no prep surface. Also of note in shakedown passes Joe was used to leaving on the yellow lights and never gave a thought at this event it was instant green. Well that's a problem seeing he can't see the green light with his hat sticking through the hood and when in the other lane the A pillar was in the way so he literally had to wait for the other guy to leave!! He joked about making a peanut butter and jelly sandwich at the tree before launching. They made some seat adjustments and by the fourth run he was able to cut a light but as Joe said he's just out to make a couple passes and have some fun and that he did making four passes before blowing a burst panel ending his night. You can bet Joe will sort it all out and be back in full force as he plans to compete in the next No Prep King in Norwalk.  #dauntlessdaytona #joezolper #noprepkingsrt66

title: Watch Street Outlaws' Lizzy Musi Funeral Livestream Here...
description:
The racing world was deeply saddened when Lizzy Musi, a beloved racer from "Street Outlaws: No Prep Kings," passed away at the age of 33. Her sudden death was announced by her father, Pat Musi, on social media. The post stated, "Surrounded by her family, in the comfort of her own home, Lizzy was called to heaven." The family requested privacy to grieve and make arrangements.

As time has passed, fans have wondered if there will be a public memorial service where they can pay their respects. While the memorial service for Lizzy will not be open to the public, it will be broadcasted live so that fans can join in honoring her life. The service will be live-streamed on July 2, 2024, starting at 2 p.m. EST. Fans can watch the broadcast on the website of Cavin Cook Funeral Home and Crematory in Mooresville, N.C. Lizzyâ€™s family and friends have encouraged the public to join the live broadcast. Pat Musi shared, "Please join us today as we come together to honor our daughter. Thank you all." #StreetOutlaws #LizzyMusi #Funeral

Street Outlaws: No Prep Kings" is a thrilling spin-off of the popular "Street Outlaws" series, featuring a unique and challenging format of drag racing. Unlike traditional races on prepared tracks, no prep races take place on surfaces without the usual traction enhancements, making for unpredictable and high-stakes competitions. The show follows elite street racers from across the country as they compete in a series of events at various tracks, aiming to claim the coveted title of No Prep King. With its intense races, diverse competitors, and the added element of raw, unprepped tracks, "No Prep Kings" delivers high-octane excitement and showcases the skill and daring of the best street racers in the nation

National Trail Raceway is a renowned drag racing track located in Hebron, Ohio, known for its rich history and vibrant motorsports culture. Established in 1964, this quarter-mile track has been a premier destination for drag racing enthusiasts, hosting a variety of events from grassroots races to major national competitions. With its well-maintained facilities, enthusiastic crowds, and a calendar packed with exciting events, National Trail Raceway offers a thrilling experience for both racers and spectators. title: Reimagining the VW Bus: Volkswagen ID Buzz, Best Vehicle Brand Awards, and Car Community Events
description:
What if an iconic vehicle from the past could be reimagined for a sustainable future? Join us as we chat with John Vincent from US News & World Report about the buzz surrounding Volkswagen's nostalgic yet modern ID Buzz. This electric tribute to the classic VW bus is stirring emotions with its retro design, but it also has us debating its limited range and significant price point. We also navigate through Volkswagen's post-Dieselgate journey, discussing their refreshed lineup, including the revamped Tiguan that says goodbye to the third-row seat.

Shift gears with us as we celebrate the winners of the Best Vehicle Brand Awards. We explore Honda's unwavering commitment to sedans, with the beloved Accord and Civic models standing strong amidst an SUV-dominated market. Hyundai impresses with its affordable and stylish SUV offerings like the Kona and Santa Fe, while the luxurious ride of the Ram 1500 and 2500 earns them a top spot in the pickup category. Meanwhile, Texas is bustling with automotive events, from the Grand Central Park Car Show to the thrilling endurance races at MSR Houston, offering a perfect blend of cars, community, and camaraderie. Whether you're a car enthusiast or just curious, this episode promises engaging insights and lively discussions.
